7 (A) (1) IN THIS SECTION THE FOLLOWING WORDS HAVE THE MEANINGS
8 INDICATED.
9 (2) “CONTRACTOR” MEANS A PERSON, OTHER THAN AN EMPLOYEE
10 OF AN OWNER, WHO PERFORMS OR OFFERS OR AGREES TO PERFORM ANY OF THE
11 FOLLOWING FOR AN OWNER:
12 (I) THE ADDITION TO OR ALTERATION, CONVERSION,
13 IMPROVEMENT, MODERNIZATION, REMODELING, REPAIR, OR REPLACEMENT OF A
14 BUILDING OR PART OF A BUILDING, OTHER THAN NEW CONSTRUCTION, THAT IS
15 USED OR DESIGNED TO BE USED AS A RESIDENCE OR A STRUCTURE ADJACENT TO
16 THAT BUILDING;
17 (II) AN IMPROVEMENT TO LAND ADJACENT TO THE RESIDENCE;
18 (III) CONSTRUCTION, IMPROVEMENT, OR REPLACEMENT, ON
19 LAND ADJACENT TO THE RESIDENCE, OF A DRIVEWAY, FALL–OUT SHELTER, FENCE,
20 GARAGE, LANDSCAPING, DECK, PIER, PORCH, OR SWIMMING POOL;
21 (IV) A SHORE EROSION CONTROL PROJECT, AS DEFINED UNDER
22 § 8–1001 OF THE NATURAL RESOURCES ARTICLE, FOR A RESIDENTIAL PROPERTY;
23 (V) CONNECTION, INSTALLATION, OR REPLACEMENT IN THE
24 RESIDENCE OF A DISHWASHER, DISPOSAL, OR REFRIGERATOR WITH AN ICEMAKER
25 TO EXISTING EXPOSED HOUSEHOLD PLUMBING LINES;
26 (VI) INSTALLATION IN THE RESIDENCE OF AN AWNING, FIRE
27 ALARM, OR STORM WINDOW; OR
28 (VII) WORK DONE ON INDIVIDUAL CONDOMINIUM UNITS.

HOUSE BILL 1348 3
1 (3) (I) “DISASTER” MEANS A SERIOUS EVENT THAT CAUSES HARM
2 TO A HOME, BUILDING, OR OTHER STRUCTURE.
3 (II) “DISASTER” INCLUDES A FIRE, FLOOD, HURRICANE, OR
4 OTHER NATURAL EVENT THAT CAUSES HARM.
5 (B) THIS SECTION DOES NOT APPLY TO A CONTRACTOR, OR A PERSON
6 ACTING ON BEHALF OF A CONTRACTOR, WHO IS ENGAGED IN AN ONGOING BUSINESS
7 RELATIONSHIP, OTHER THAN MERE SOLICITATION, WITH A VICTIM OF A DISASTER
8 BEFORE THE DISASTER OCCURS.
9 (C) FOR PURPOSES OF THIS SECTION, THE EXISTENCE OF A DISASTER IS
10 NOT CONTINGENT ON THE DECLARATION OF A STATE OF EMERGENCY BY THE
11 FEDERAL GOVERNMENT OR THE GOVERNOR UNDER § 14–107 OF THE PUBLIC
12 SAFETY ARTICLE, OR A LOCAL DISASTER DECLARATION AS DEFINED UNDER §
13 14–110.5 OF THE PUBLIC SAFETY ARTICLE.
14 (D) A CONTRACTOR, OR A PERSON ACTING ON BEHALF OF A CONTRACTOR,
15 MAY NOT SOLICIT OR ATTEMPT TO SOLICIT A DISASTER VICTIM WITHIN 48 HOURS
16 AFTER A DISASTER.
17 (E) A VIOLATION OF SUBSECTION (D) OF THIS SECTION IS:
18 (1) AN UNFAIR, ABUSIVE, OR DECEPTIVE TRADE PRACTICE, AS
19 DEFINED UNDER TITLE 13 OF THIS ARTICLE; AND
20 (2) SUBJECT TO THE ENFORCEMENT AND PENALTY PROVISIONS OF
21 TITLE 13 OF THIS ARTICLE.
22 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
23 October 1, 2025.

